ds'', Simon and Schuster, 2015 {{ISBN|1471150976}}.\n* [[Taliaferro Preston Shaffner|Shaffner, Taliaferro Preston]], [https://archive.org/stream/telegraphmanualc00shafrich#page/n3/mode/2up ''The Telegraph Manual''], Pudney & Russell, 1859.\n* [[Willoughby Smith|Smith, Willoughby]], [https://archive.org/details/riseandextensio00smitgoog ''The Rise and Extension of Submarine Telegraphy''], London:  J.S. Virtue & Co., 1891 {{oclc|1079820592}}.\n* Stephenson, Charles, ''The Fortifications of Malta 1530\u20131945'', Bloomsbury Publishing, 2012 {{ISBN|9781849080156}}.\n* Thomas, William Arthur, ''The Provincial Stock Exchanges'', Routledge, 2012 {{ISBN|9780714629810}} (1973 reprint).\n* [[Silvanus P. Thompson|Thompson, Silvanus Phillips]], ''The Life of Lord Kelvin'', vol. 1, American Mathematical Society, 2004 {{ISBN|9780821837436}} (first published 1910).\n* Walker, Peter M., \"Contract\", ''The Solicitors' Journal'', vol. 142, 1998.\n* Welch, Dick; Fr\u00e9mond, Olivier (eds), ''The Case-by-case Approach to Privatization'', World Bank Publications, 1998 {{ISBN|9780821341964}}.\n* Wenzlhuemer, Roland, ''Connecting the Nineteenth-Century World: The Telegraph and Globalization'', Cambridge University Press, 2013 {{ISBN|1107025281}}.\n* Williams, Liz, ''Kind Regards: The Lost Art of Letter Writing'', Michael O'Mara Books, 2012 {{ISBN|1843177137}}.\n* Winseck, Dwayne R.; Pike, Robert M., ''Communication and Empire'', Duke University Press, 2007 {{ISBN|9780822389996}}.\n* Whitelaw, ''Whitelaw's Telegraph Cyphers'', London: Whitelaw's Telegraph Cypher Co., 1904 {{oclc|820084531}}.\n\n[[Category:History of the telegraph]]\n[[Category:History of telecommunications in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:General Post Office]]\n", "name_user": "Spinningspark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMilitary:spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_telegraphy_in_the_United_Kingdom"}
{"title_page": "Jason Nash", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor, writer, director, comedian, podcaster, and YouTube personality}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=October 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name        = Jason Nash\n| image        = Jason Nash.jpg\n| image_size   = \n| caption      = \n| birth_name   =  Jason Eric Nash\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1973|05|23}}<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DavidDobrik|author=DAVID DOBRIK|number=867165980513849344|date=23 May 2017|title=Happy birthday to one of my favorite seniors. Thank you for letting me broadcast your mid life crisis to the world}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], U.S.\n| occupation   = {{flatlist|\n* Actor\n* YouTube personality\n}} \n| spouse       =  Marney Hochman (divorced)\n| years_active = 2016\u2013present\n| subscribers= 2.5 million (Jason Nash) <br> 218k (Jason Nash Family)\n| views=405 million (Jason Nash) <br> 9.7 million (Jason Nash Family)\n| network = Collab\n| associated_acts =* [[Josh Peck]]\n* [[David Dobrik & \"The Vlog Squad\"|David Dobrik]]\n* [[Trisha Paytas]]\n* [[Gabbie Hanna]]\n* [[Liza Koshy]]\n* [[JoJo Siwa]]\n| silver_button=yes\n| silver_year=2017\n|gold_button=yes\n|gold_year=2018\n| stats_update = {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}\n| alma_mater    = \n}}\n\n'''Jason Eric Nash''' (born May 23, 1973) is an American actor and [[YouTube]] personality. Best known for his channel on [[Vine (service)|Vine]], he was also a semi-finalist on ''[[Last Comic Standing]]'' in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jason Nash on Last Comic Standing|url=http://tvgeekarmy.com/post/viewpost/last-comic-standing-week-five-monkey-at-the-controls|website=TVGeekArmy.com|accessdate=July 11, 2010}}</ref> In 2016, Nash co-produced and starred in the movie, ''FML'' alongside friend and fellow YouTuber Brandon Calvillo.\n\n==Career==\nJason Nash moved to Los Angeles with the aspiration of becoming a comedian and instead met David Dobrik. Years into his life in Los Angeles, Nash built a presence on Vine and had over two million followers.<ref>(n.d.). Retrieved from httpd://vine.co/Jason Nash/</ref> This was his first crack at the social media world, before becoming a YouTube later on in his career.  Nash trained with the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]] and started his career as a member of the sketch troupe \"Price, Nash and Blindside\". The trio developed television shows for [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] and [[NBC]] and were chosen three times to perform at the [[Aspen Comedy Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nash with Upright Citizens Brigade|url=http://www.cc.com/shows/upright-citizens-brigade|publisher=Comedy Central}}</ref>\n\nNash wrote, directed and starred in his [[Comedy Central]] web series \"Jason Nash Is Married\", which was based on his one-man show \"In the Land of Tall Buildings and Red Fire Engines\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-jason-nash-is-married-review-20140905-story.html|title=Fun 'Jason Nash Is Married' explores love and showbiz|last=Goldstein|first=Gary|website=latimes.com|access-date=2018-04-06}}</ref> A film version of \"Jason Nash Is Married\" was released in 2014 starring [[Busy Philipps]].<ref>{{Citation|last=Nash|first=Jason|title=Jason Nash Is Married|date=2014-06-24|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3737782/|others=Jason Nash, Busy Philipps, Casey Wilson|accessdate=2018-04-06}}</ref> Nash also created the web series \"How to Be a Man and The Shaman\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thelaughbutton.com/interviews/jason-nash-says-fml-new-indie-comedy/|title=Jason Nash says \"FML\" in his new indie comedy -|website=thelaughbutton.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-06}}</ref> In 2016, Nash starred and directed his own screenplay, a road trip comedy film \"FML\" featuring fellow Vine star Brandon Calvillo.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/jason-nash-brandon-calvillo-fml-vine-1201743390/|title=Vine Stars Jason Nash, Brandon Calvillo Join Road Trip Comedy \u2018FML\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=2016-03-31|work=Variety|access-date=2018-04-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nNash co-created the long-running podcast \"Guys with Feelings\" which debuted in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jason Nash, a Guy with Feelings|url=http://laist.com/2008/12/11/interview_jason_nash.php|publisher=laist.com|accessdate=11 December 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081214135920/http://laist.com/2008/12/11/interview_jason_nash.php|archivedate=14 December 2008}}</ref> He has developed shows for Fox, NBC,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0621738/|title=Jason Nash|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-04-06}}</ref> [[CBS]], [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] and IFC. He has also acted in various shows including an opening of ''[[House MD]]'' episode 'The Tyrant', ''[[The Simpsons]]'' and ''[[Drake & Josh]].''  Nash is currently a YouTube [[vlogger]], and has over 2.5 million subscribers on his main channel.<ref>U. (n.d.). JasonNashComedy YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics. Retrieved from https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/jasonnashcomedy</ref> Nash became a Youtube Vlogger after being discovered by fellow Viner, [[David Dobrik & \"The Vlog Squad\"|David Dobrik]], one night at a comedy club. He began his Youtube career as a character in David Dobrik's vlogs, and soon began to upload his own videos. His first video was uploaded on December 2, 2016.<ref>Nash, J. (2016, December 02). Retrieved November 01, 2018, from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ubgAC-5wF2A</ref>\n\nNash also runs a weekly podcast named \"Views\" with fellow YouTube personality David Dobrik. During its debut in 2017, \"Views\" climbed to #3 on the iTunes charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shortyawards.com/10th/jasonnash|title=Jason Nash - The Shorty Awards|website=shortyawards.com|access-date=2018-04-06}}</ref>  Jason Nash and David Dobrik also took their podcast on a live tour across the US in summer of 2018, with their fellow youtube friends, called the \"Vlog Squad\".<ref>VIEWS SUMMER TOUR 2018. (n.d.). Retrieved from http://viewstour.com/</ref> They called it the \"VIEWS\" Tour. This included performances from other Youtubers such as Scotty Sire, live stories and a live Q&A session.<ref>Weiss, G. (2018, May 15). Vlogger/Podcasters David Dobrik And Jason Nash To Kick Off Summer Tour. Retrieved from https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/05/15/david-dobrik-and-jason-nash-views-tour/</ref>  Nash has stated that he is focused on Youtube as his career and because of this he uploads multiple times a week. For approximately one year, Nash had a second channel titled \"Jason Nash Family\" dedicated to his life with his children, Charley and Wyatt.<ref>(n.d.). Retrieved November 01, 2018, from https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWcVikU5Sv-AqMtjV-BVsLQ</ref> This channel was later shut down by the request of his ex-wife Marney, who requested that the children would not be on the internet in such a drastic way. Because of this, Nash has put all his attention to his main Youtube channel.\n\n==Personal life==\nNash graduated from [[Medfield High School]] in 1991 and then attended college at the [[University of Massachusetts Amherst]]. After he left college, he worked as an assistant to [[Norm Macdonald]] on  ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''. Nash moved to Hollywood in 2001 when he was cast on the sketch show Random Play for [[VH1]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.laweekly.com/arts/how-jason-nash-makes-a-living-in-web-series-4254799|title=How Jason Nash Makes a Living in Web Series|last=Carrie|first=Stephanie|date=2014-02-18|work=L.A. Weekly|access-date=2018-04-06}}</ref>\n\nHe was in a relationship with fellow Youtuber [[Trisha Paytas]]. The couple began dating in 2018, but were reported to have separated in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Newsweek]]|url=https://www.newsweek.com/trisha-paytas-david-dobrik-twitter-jason-nash-1317335|title=YouTuber Trisha Paytas Calls Out David Dobrik and Vlog Squad for Manipulation|date=February 4, 2019|author=Asarch, Steven|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190527031338/https://www.newsweek.com/trisha-paytas-david-dobrik-twitter-jason-nash-1317335|archive-date=May 27, 2019|access-date=August 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn May 15, 2019, fellow YouTuber [[David Dobrik]] legally married Lorraine Nash, Nash's mother, as a [[Sketch comedy|bit]] for one of his vlogs. On June 12, 2019, Dobrik announced that he and Lorraine had decided to end their marriage after one month. On November 22, 2019, Dobrik stated via Instagram that he has officially signed divorce papers and divorced Nash.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television and film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Drake & Josh]]''\n| Waiter\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n| Neighbor\n|\n|-\n|2007\u20132010\n|''[[SuperNews!]]''\n| Multiple Characters \n|\n|-\n|2014\n|''Jason Nash is Married''\n| Jason Nash\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[The Simpsons]]''\n| Southie Criminals / Philantrophic Southies \n| Season 28, Episode 3: \"[[The Town (The Simpsons)|The Town]]\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/JasonNashComedy Jason Nash Comedy YouTube Channel]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nash, Jason}}\n[[Category:Amherican male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Writers from Boston]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Vine celebrities]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor, writer, director, comedian, podcaster, and YouTube personality}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=October 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name        = Jason Nash\n| image        = Jason Nash.jpg\n| image_size   = \n| caption      = \n| birth_name   =  Jason Eric Nash\n| birth_date 