{"title_page": "List of North American rapid transit systems by ridership", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{See also|List of United States rapid transit systems by ridership|List of North American light rail systems by ridership}}\nThis is a '''list of North American rapid transit systems by ridership.''' These [[Passenger rail terminology#Heavy rail|heavy rail]] or [[rapid transit]] systems are also known as ''metro'' or ''subway'' systems. This list of systems in [[North America]] does not include [[light rail]], even when they are integrated with heavy rail. Daily and annual ridership figures are based on \"average weekday ''unlinked'' passenger trips\" (where transfers between lines are counted as two separate passenger \"boardings\" or \"trips\"), unless otherwise indicated (e.g., Mexico City and Monterrey, whose figures are the average for ''all'' days, not just weekdays). For metro systems in the United States (including Puerto Rico) and Canada, the annual ridership figures for 2018 and average weekday ridership figures for the Fourth Quarter (Q4) of 2018 come from the [[American Public Transportation Association]]'s (APTA) ridership reports statistics,<ref name=\"APTA-2014-Q4\" /> unless otherwise noted. Ridership figures for Mexico come from Banco de Informaci\u00f3n Econ\u00f3mica's INEGI reports for the year 2018.<ref name=\"INEGI\" />\n__NOTOC__\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!\n! width=\"125px\" | System\n! width=\"110px\" | Country\n! City/area<br />served\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Annual<br />ridership<br /><small>(2018)</small><ref name=\"APTA-2014-Q4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.apta.com/resources/statistics/Documents/Ridership/2018-Q4-Ridership-APTA.pdf|title=Transit Ridership Report Fourth Quarter and End-of-Year 2018|date=April 12, 2019|publisher=[[American Public Transportation Association]] (APTA)|format=pdf|via=https://www.apta.com/research-technical-resources/transit-statistics/ridership-report/ridership-report-archives/|accessdate=2019-04-21}}</ref><ref name=\"INEGI\">{{cite web | url = http://www.inegi.org.mx/sistemas/bie/ | title = Banco de Informaci\u00f3n Econ\u00f3mica \u2013 Instituto Nactional De Estad\u00edstica Y Geograf\u00eda \u2013 Comunicaciones y transportes | publisher = Instituto Nactional De Estad\u00edstica Y Geograf\u00eda (INEGI) | date = March 2015 | accessdate = 2014-04-01}}</ref>\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Avg. daily<br />weekday<br />boardings<br /><small>(Q4 2018)</small><ref name=\"APTA-2014-Q4\" /><ref name=\"INEGI\" />\n! width=\"65px\" | System<br />length\n! Avg. daily<br />boardings<br />per mile<br /><small>(Q4 2018)</small>\n!  data-sort-type=\"number\" | Year<br />opened\n!  data-sort-type=\"number\" | Stations\n!  data-sort-type=\"number\" | Lines\n|-\n| 1\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[New York City Subway]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flag|USA}} \n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[New York City]]\n| 2,629,594,200\n| 8,764,700\n| {{convert|232|mi|km|sortable=on}}<ref name=\"mtabudget\">{{cite web |url=http://web.mta.info/mta/investor/pdf/2012/2012-Comprehensive-Annual-Financial-Report.pdf |title=Comprehensive Annual Financial Report for the Years Ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 |publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority|Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA)]] |format=pdf |page=146 |date=June 21, 2013 |accessdate=2014-08-29}}</ref>\n| 37,778\n| 1904<ref group=\"note\">The current system incorporates elevated sections built in 1870.</ref>\n| 472<ref name=\"nyct\">{{cite web |url=http://web.mta.info/mta/network.htm#statsnyct |title=The MTA Network \u2013 New York City Transit at a Glance |publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]] |date= |accessdate=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n| 24<ref name=\"nyct\"/>\n|-\n| 2\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Mexico City Metro]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flag|Mexico}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Mexico City]]\n| 1,591,984,000<ref group=\"note\" name=\"average-year\">This ''Annual Ridership'' figure for 2014 is obtained by averaging the ''Average Daily Ridership'' for the twelve months in 2014, and then multiplying that figure by the number of days in a year.</ref>\n| 4,361,600<ref group=\"note\" name=\"average-day\">This is the ''Average Daily Ridership'' figure, '''''not''''' an Average ''Weekday'' Ridership figure \u2013 it is averaged from the Q4 2014 Total Ridership figure for this system.</ref>\n| {{convert|140.75|mi|km|1|sortable=on}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/operacion/cifrasoperacion.html |title=Datos de operacion |publisher=Metro de la Ciudad de Mexico |language=Spanish |trans-title=Operational data |accessdate=2014-04-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014104236/http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/operacion/cifrasoperacion.html |archivedate=2013-10-14 }}</ref>\n| 30,988\n| 1969\n| 195<ref name=\"MC-data\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/operacion/cifrasoperacion.html |title=Datos de operacion |publisher=Metro de la Ciudad de Mexico |language=Spanish |trans-title=Operational data |accessdate=2013-10-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014104236/http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/operacion/cifrasoperacion.html |archivedate=2013-10-14 }}</ref> \n| 12<ref name=\"MC-data\" />\n|-\n|3\n|[[Toronto subway]]<ref name=\"Toronto\" group=\"note\">Totals represent the sum of the \"Heavy Rail (HR)\" and \"Intermediate Rail (IR)\" figures for Toronto from the APTA ridership report \u2013 in other words, figures include stations and ridership on [[Line 3 Scarborough|Line 3 Scarborough (RT)]], which APTA considers to be an IR line and which the [[Toronto Transit Commission|local transit authority]] includes in the rapid transit system for mapping and administrative purposes.</ref>\n|{{flag|Canada}}\n|[[Toronto]]\n|416,210,500\n|1,343,600\n|{{convert|47.8|mi|km|sortable=on}}<ref name=\"TTC-stats\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ttc.ca/About_the_TTC/Operating_S